{"name": "ilpy", "metadata": {"name": "ilpy", "version": "0.4.1", "classifiers": [], "home_page": null, "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Python wrappers for popular MIP solvers.", "upload_time": 1729852006}, "documentation": ["# ilpy\n\n[![License](https://img.shields.io/pypi/l/ilpy.svg)](https://github.com/funkelab/ilpy/raw/main/LICENSE)\n[![Anaconda](https://img.shields.io/conda/v/funkelab/ilpy)](https://anaconda.org/funkelab/ilpy)\n[![PyPI](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/ilpy.svg)](https://pypi.org/project/ilpy)\n[![CI](https://github.com/funkelab/ilpy/actions/workflows/ci.yaml/badge.svg)](https://github.com/funkelab/ilpy/actions/workflows/ci.yaml)\n[![codecov](https://codecov.io/gh/funkelab/ilpy/branch/main/graph/badge.svg)](https://codecov.io/gh/funkelab/ilpy)\n\nUnified python wrappers for popular ILP solvers\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\nconda install -c funkelab ilpy\n```\n\n## Local development\n\nilpy links against SCIP, so you must have SCIP installed in your environment.\n(You can install via conda)\n\n```bash\nconda install scip==9.1.0\n```\n\nThen clone the repo and install in editable mode.\n\n```bash\ngit clone <your-fork>\ncd ilpy\npip install -e .[dev]\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "setup", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "setup.CYTHON_TRACE", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "setup.libraries", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "setup.include_dirs", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "setup.library_dirs", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "setup.compile_args", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "setup.GUROBI_LIB", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "setup.wrapper", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "ilpy", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "ilpy.__getattr__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "name", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "function